==English==
===Noun===
'''wanker'''

#(''British, vulgar slang, rare'') A person (usually male) who [[wank]]s.
#(''British, vulgar slang'') A stupid or ineffectual person.
Wank is a slang term for [[masturbation]], thus a wanker is one who masturbates. Beyond the general, [[secular]] acceptance of masturbation as normal behaviour, it is stilled viewed with some trepidation as evidenced by the [[aspertion]] to convey stupidity. Generally applied to males, it is gaining "popularity" among females for the same purpose. Female masturbation in recent years has also been termed "wanking" although traditionally assigned to the male act. The word is a fairly heavy insult and although it may be used almost affectionately among friends with [[robust]] realtionships, it has not really lost it's insulting nature and the meaning has not become [[vague]] as with other slang. A lesser version of the word would be "tosser" or "tosspot" which carry the same general meaning but have less impact and thus are more socially "acceptable".


====Synonyms====
*(2): (''US'') [[jerk]], [[jerkoff]], (''British'') [[tosser]], [[tosspot]]

====Usage note====
*This word is rarely used in its literal sense of "one who wanks".

